<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ACCIDENT KILLS BOY DRIVING STOLEN CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 15-year-old Sun Valley boy driving a stolen automobile was killed Friday when 
the car struck a tree in North Hollywood, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Four other juveniles, ages 14 and 15, fled the scene, but one of them later 
walked into the North Hollywood police station and gave detectives information 
about the accident. 
</P>
<P>
The 15-year-old North Hollywood boy was questioned and taken into custody on 
suspicion of auto theft, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Bruce Herschong said the car involved in the accident was stolen about a 
month ago from a West Los Angeles street. The car was traveling west on Stagg 
Street at 8:30 a.m. when it struck the curb on the north side of the street, 
hit a tree, spun around and halted next to a fence, Herschong said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver died at the scene and witnesses said the other youths fled. The 
informant was cut and bruised in the accident and said the other youths 
suffered similar injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Herschong said the driver had not been drinking and was not speeding when the 
accident occurred. 
