<TEXT>
<P>
Any Dodger fan would admit that a scan of the team's statistics in the morning 
paper is enough to ruin a good cup of coffee. 
</P>
<P>
Let's face it, last year it was Kirk Gibson. This year it's Eddie Murray. The 
Dodgers are not a one-man team, they are a team that has simply forgotten they 
are still this year's world champions. 
</P>
<P>
RAUL MARTINEZ 
</P>
<P>
Northridge 
