FRED ROGGIN'S HUMOR BELONGS IN LOCKER ROOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I agree with Larry Stewart's comments regarding Fred Roggin's penchant for low 
humor. 
</P>
<P>
Another factor that detracts from Roggin's work is his ongoing lack of respect 
for women. If a bikini-clad woman is in attendance at a sporting event, Roggin 
will comment: 
</P>
<P>
 -- There will be no tittering about this play. 
</P>
<P>
 -- The play was busted up. 
</P>
<P>
 -- It's a good day for a doubleheader. 
</P>
<P>
 -- He's just trying to keep us abreast of sports. 
</P>
<P>
One expects humor like this in a junior high locker room, but it has no place 
in a news broadcast. 
</P>
<P>
CHARLES GOULD 
</P>
