<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRANGE OUT OF RANGE FOR THE AVERAGE DUFFER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In all my golf experiences I have never heard the expression a Red Grange, 
which was referred to in the June 6 Morning Briefing. 
</P>
<P>
Perhaps this is because, in my circles, if someone were to shoot a Red Grange 
(a 77, after Grange's uniform number) he would be either deified or accused of 
altering his scorecard. 
</P>
<P>
Therefore, as the self-proclaimed voice of the average duffer, I offer a new 
terminology to the world of golf, a phrase that might soon be heard on the 
links of America with alarming frequency: I just had a Mark Gastineau (No. 99). 
</P>
<P>
DANA MERINO 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
