<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNMODEST $53 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I enjoyed Paul Grein's May 31 article on Bette Midler and the success she and 
the "Beaches" sound track album have earned. However, I do take umbrage at one 
paragraph: "The smash success of the . . . album is surprising because the film 
. . . was only a modest hit and has long since disappeared from movie screens." 
</P>
<P>
The May 31 Daily Variety Film Boxoffice Report lists "Beaches" at No. 11 and 
still making money with a plus 163% change and grossing well over $53 million 
in 160 days since its release. There's nothing "modest" about $53 million. 
</P>
<P>
The movie is still playing on 345 screens and just opened to good reviews in 
Britain and Australia. 
</P>
<P>
GARRY MARSHALL 
</P>
<P>
Director, "Beaches" 
</P>
<P>
Walt Disney Pictures 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
