<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: RECOUNT CONFIRMS OUSTER OF VICE MAYOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A recount on Friday of the votes in a May 23 recall election, in which San 
Gabriel Vice Mayor Frank Blaszcak lost his City Council seat by a nine-vote 
margin, has confirmed the results, said Deputy City Clerk Cindy Bookter. 
</P>
<P>
"It was on the nose," said Bookter, the official in charge of the 
election-night tally. "They (Blaszcak's supporters) may not be happy about it, 
but I believe they're satisfied. I hope their faith has been restored in (the 
city clerk's) office. I feel so happy about this." 
</P>
<P>
Supporters of Blaszcak, who was accused of abusing his powers as a city 
official, have called for an investigation by the Los Angeles County district 
attorney, the secretary of state and the attorney general, claiming there may 
have been ballot-tampering. The final count was 1,903 for recall and 1,894 
against. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Meredith, a spokesman for Friends of Frank Blaszcak, said that the recount 
had not changed his opinion that an investigation should be conducted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
