<TEXT>
<P>
Akins Development Co., a smaller Orange County home builder, said it is making 
its first move into San Bernardino and Riverside counties with $50 million 
worth of new homes in San Bernardino's Rancho Cucamonga. 
</P>
<P>
Akins said it will build 145 homes with prices set to start in the low $300,000 
range. The smaller builder is doing the project as a joint venture with the 
massive William Lyon Co. 
</P>
<P>
Akins has already built extensively in Orange County but, like other local home 
builders, has been drawn to the cheaper land and livelier housing markets of 
the two inland counties. 
